data.title: GG19 - Web3 OSS
data.description: We are participating in Gitcoin Round 19 (GG19).

We will invest the money into a partnership with an aggregator of financial data, for example [DeFiLlama](https://defillama.com) or [TokenUnlocks](https://token.unlocks.app).

In the end, we want Militereum to be more than a firewall that warns you for technical issues with your transactions.

We want Militereum to be a financial firewall, warning you for financial risks, for example: when you are about to buy a token with a huge token unlock coming up.
data.title: If we receive more than $1000

data.description:
We will pay [our designer](https://www.linkedin.com/in/melindaberki) for the [awesome website she build for us](https://militereum.com), plus we will ask her to design version 2.0 of our web site.

Our future website needs to attract more n00bs and make it easier for them to set Militereum up.
data.title: If we receive $501 - $1000

data.description:
Militereum needs [metamorphic contract](https://0age.medium.com/the-promise-and-the-peril-of-metamorphic-contracts-9eb8b8413c5e) detection, because those smart contracts could be updated to divert your money elsewhere.

We will translate a16z's [Metamorphic Contract Detector](https://github.com/a16z/metamorphic-contract-detector) from Python to Delphi.

Once translated, we will open source the Delphi implementation and make it available for free to the Delphi community at large.
data.title: If we receive up to $500

We will want to warn our users for a high dumping risk. This risk has a high probability if a private wallet owns more than 5% of the total supply. A sale of such size could greatly affect the token’s price and we will want to warn our users for such risk. To be included with Militereum in Q3, 2024.

data.description: We will want to write unit tests for every step taking place while Militereum checks your transaction. Currently, [we have a few unit tests](https://github.com/Militereum/Militereum/blob/main/checks.tests.pas) but by no means do we have 100% coverage. By the end of the Q3, 2024 there should be a unit test for every step.
data.title: Unit tests for every step

data.description: We have partnered with [vaults.fyi](https://www.vaults.fyi), the homepage of onchain yield. When you are about to deposit tokens into a yield-bearing vault, but another vault earns you higher yield while holding the same TVL (or more), Militereum will warn you about the situation and help you find out about the other vault.
data.title: vaults.fyi partnership

data.description: We have partnered with [Revoke.Cash](https://revoke.cash/) to bring you Auto-Revoke, a groundbreaking feature for your crypto security. Auto-Revoke automatically revokes allowances when they are no longer needed, ensuring top-notch protection. [Click here to read more about Auto-Revoke](https://svanas.medium.com/introducing-auto-revoke-dba9f3222414).
data.title: Revoke.Cash partnership

data.text: The revoke.cash [PR is here](https://github.com/Militereum/Militereum/pull/11) and the vaults.fyi [PR is here](https://github.com/Militereum/Militereum/pull/12). Both PRs have been merged.
data.title: PRs for revoke.cash and vaults.fyi have been merged

questions.query: How does your project contribute significantly to the Ethereum network's infrastructure? Please provide specific examples and metrics if available.
questions.explanation: While we don't have metrics (because our product does not include any telemetry by design), we do know that it prevents n00bs and OGs from getting phished, hacked, drained or rugged. Because they frequently tell us.

questions.query: Describe any pioneering development work in your project, particularly in enhancing privacy, interoperability, or user experience.
questions.explanation: We are the one and only wallet security extension that works with every crypto wallet out there, including browser-based wallets and native desktop wallets.

questions.query: What specific problems or challenges in the Ethereum ecosystem does your project address? How does your solution improve upon existing alternatives?
questions.explanation: Most security add-ons for your wallets are browser extensions. We are not going to shit on them, but the web browser is a hostile environment/host for security extensions. We are the one and only native app in the industry, audited by Microsoft and Apple App Store auditors.

questions.query: Outline your project's roadmap and how the grant funds will be used to achieve your development goals.
questions.explanation: We have big plans for the future, including a mobile version and AI scanning your transactions before they leave your device.

questions.query: How does your project contribute to the decentralization and security of the Ethereum network?
questions.explanation: Fewer hacks. Fewer drains. Fewer victims of rug pulls. Honestly, if we ever want to succeed as an industry, n00bs do need to get protected from this nonsense. Or we will never reach mass adoption.
